'''無性戀'''，也稱為'''无性爱'''{{notetag|日韩地区}}（{{lang-en|Asexuality}}），是指認為他人缺乏<!-- NOTE: Reliable sources often state "lack," and the term is broader than "absence of" or "no" sexual attraction. See the "Definition, identity and relationships" section below. Furthermore, "absent" is already included in this very first sentence.-->[[性感|性吸引]]力，或是缺乏或有著低度[[性欲|性欲]]的狀態。<ref name="Crooks">{{cite book|authors=Robert L. Crooks, Karla Baur|title=Our Sexuality|isbn=1305887425|publisher={{tsl|en|Cengage Learning||Cengage Learning}}|year=2016|page=300|accessdate=2017-01-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=isIaCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT300}}</ref><ref name="Helm">{{cite book|author=Katherine M. Helm|title=Hooking Up: The Psychology of Sex and Dating|isbn=1610699513|publisher={{tsl|en|ABC-CLIO||ABC-CLIO}}|year=2015|page=32|accessdate=2017-01-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=O3K9CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA32|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122195144/https://books.google.com/books?id=O3K9CgAAQBAJ&pg=PA32|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Kelly">{{cite book|last = Kelly| first = Gary F.|authormask = |authorlink =|title = Sexuality Today: The Human Perspective|url =|edition=7|series =|year = 2004 | publisher = {{tsl|en|McGraw-Hill||McGraw-Hill}} |location=|isbn= 978-0-07-255835-7|oclc = |doi =|bibcode =|id =|page = 401|pages=| nopp =| at =|chapter  = Chapter 12 | chapterurl=|quote =|ref =| laysummary =|laydate =|separator=|postscript =   Asexuality is a condition characterized by a low interest in sex.|lastauthoramp =}}</ref>有些說法認為這和[[异性恋|异性恋]]、[[同性戀|同性戀]]、[[双性恋|双性恋]]等一樣是一種性取向；另一些則認為無性戀是「[[性取向|性取向]]並不存在」。<ref name = Bogaert2004>{{cite journal|last=Bogaert|first=Anthony F. |year=2004 |title=Asexuality: prevalence and associated factors in a national probability sample |journal=[[性研究期刊|Journal of Sex Research]] |volume=41 |issue=3 |pages=279–87|pmid=15497056 |doi=10.1080/00224490409552235}}</ref><ref name="Sexual orientation">{{cite journal|last=Melby|first=Todd|title=Asexuality gets more attention, but is it a sexual orientation?|journal=Contemporary Sexuality|date=November 2005|volume=39|issue=11|pages=1, 4–5 | issn = 1094-5725|url = http://www.apositive.org/wordpress_backup/?page_id=222|accessdate=2016-02-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106135903/http://www.apositive.org/wordpress_backup/?page_id=222 |archivedate=2015-11-06|via=the [[网站时光机|Wayback Machine]] | postscript =   [http://journalseek.net/cgi-bin/journalseek/journalsearch.cgi?field=title&query=1094-5725 The journal currently does not have a website]}}</ref><ref name="Sex and society">{{cite book|editor=Marshall Cavendish|title=Sex and Society|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|accessdate=2013-07-27|volume=2|year=2010|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7906-2|pages=82–83|contribution=Asexuality|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016040824/https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|dead-url=no}}</ref>

無性戀與[[性禁慾|性禁慾]]和[[獨身主義|獨身主義]]不同，<ref name="Halter">{{cite book|author=Margaret Jordan Halter |author2=Elizabeth M. Varcarolis|title=Varcarolis' Foundations of Psychiatric Mental Health Nursing|isbn=1-4557-5358-0|publisher=[[愛思唯爾|Elsevier Health Sciences]]|year=2013|page=382|accessdate=2014-05-07|url=https://books.google.com/?id=mZ15AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA382&dq=#v=onepage&q=&f=false}}</ref><ref name="DePaulo">{{cite web|first=Bella|last=DePaulo|title=ASEXUALS: Who Are They and Why Are They Important?|publisher=''{{tsl|en|Psychology Today||Psychology Today}}''|date=2011-09-26|accessdate=2011-12-13|url=http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/living-single/200912/asexuals-who-are-they-and-why-are-they-important|archive-date=2015-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001112720/https://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/living-single/200912/asexuals-who-are-they-and-why-are-they-important|dead-url=no}}</ref>後者是有關性行為的，且動機通常為個人性格或宗教信仰等因素。<ref>''The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language'' (3d ed. 1992), entries for ''celibacy'' and thence ''abstinence''.</ref>但性取向不等同於[[性行為|性行為]]，[[性取向|性取向]]被認為是“持久的”。<ref name="apahelp">{{cite web|title=Sexual orientation, homosexuality and bisexuality|publisher=[[美国心理学会|American Psychological Association]]|accessdate=2013-03-30|url=http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/sexual-orientation.aspx|archive-date=2013-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130808010101/http://www.apa.org/helpcenter/sexual%2Dorientation.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>一些無性戀者雖不能受到性吸引或缺少[[性慾|性慾]]，但仍會因為一些原因{{notetag|如取悅自己或伴侶，或希望繁衍後代}}，而進行性行為。<ref name="Halter"/><ref name="Prause">{{cite journal|last=Prause |first=Nicole |author2=Cynthia A. Graham |date=August 2004 |url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf |title=Asexuality: Classification and Characterization |journal={{tsl|en|Archives of Sexual Behavior||Archives of Sexual Behavior}} |volume=36 |pages=341–356 |accessdate=2007-08-31 |doi=10.1007/s10508-006-9142-3 |format=PDF |pmid=17345167 |issue=3 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927014407/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf |archivedate=2007-09-27 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

接受無性戀是一種性取向的觀點與對無性戀的[[科学方法|科學研究]]在當下仍才剛剛起步，<ref name="Helm"/><ref name="Prause"/><ref name="Sexual orientation"/>對無性戀生理和心理方面的研究正處於進展中。<ref name="Prause"/>一些研究者認為無性戀是一種性取向，但這一觀點遭到了另一些研究者的反對。<ref name="Sexual orientation"/><ref name="Sex and society"/>

自互聯網與社交媒體出現以來，許多無性戀社群得以建立，其中最著名的是無性戀能見度和教育網絡（The Asexual Visibility and Education Network），該網站於2001年由[[大衛·傑|大衛·傑]]創立。<ref name="Sex and society"/><ref name="Swash">{{cite web|first=Rosie|last=Swash|title=Among the asexuals|publisher=''[[衛報|The Guardian]]''|date=2012-02-25|accessdate=2013-02-02|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2012/feb/26/among-the-asexuals|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211010222/http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2012/feb/26/among-the-asexuals|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 無性戀者的自身認同 ==
<span data-segmentid="26" class="cx-segment">無性戀有時被稱為 ace（來自缩短"無性戀"的英文拼音<ref name="AceSuits2">{{cite book|author1=Julie Sondra Decker|title=The Invisible Orientation: An Introduction to Asexuality|date=2015|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=9781510700642|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vTSCDwAAQBAJ&dq=ace+of+hearts+asexual&q=ace+of+hearts#v=snippet&q=ace%20of%20hearts&f=false|accessdate=2019-04-20|archive-date=2020-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803043357/https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vTSCDwAAQBAJ&dq=ace+of+hearts+asexual&q=ace+of+hearts#v=snippet&q=ace%20of%20hearts&f=false|dead-url=no}}{{page number needed|date=April 2019}}</ref>），無性戀社群有時也被研究人員或無性戀者稱為ace社群''。''<span data-segmentid="27" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Meg2">{{cite book|author=Meg Barker|title=Rewriting the Rules: An Integrative Guide to Love, Sex and Relationships|isbn=978-0415517621|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2012|page=69|accessdate=2016-02-08|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Dp8_R8A2PIYC&pg=PA69|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726103159/https://books.google.com/books?id=Dp8_R8A2PIYC&pg=PA69|dead-url=no}}</ref></span></span><span data-segmentid="27" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Cerankowski and Milks">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref> 無性戀可以有很廣泛的定義，因為各個無性戀者之間可能有很大的差異。研究人員們通常將無性戀定義為不受到性吸引，或是對性行為缺乏興趣，</span><span data-segmentid="28" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Sex and society2">{{Cite book|editor-last=Marshall Cavendish|title=Asexuality|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|accessdate=2013-07-27|volume=2|year=2010|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7906-2|pages=82–83|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016040824/https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Prause2">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: Classification and Characterization|url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|last=Prause|first=Nicole|last2=Cynthia A. Graham|date=August 2004|journal=[[Archives_of_Sexual_Behavior|Archives of Sexual Behavior]]|accessdate=2007-08-31|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10508-006-9142-3|volume=36|pages=341–356|pmid=17345167|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927014407/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|archivedate=2007-09-27|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref name="Bogaert2006">{{Cite journal|title=Toward a conceptual understanding of asexuality|url=http://cat.inist.fr/?aModele=afficheN&cpsidt=18172400|last=Bogaert|first=Anthony F.|journal=[[Review_of_General_Psychology|Review of General Psychology]]|issue=3|doi=10.1037/1089-2680.10.3.241|year=2006|volume=10|pages=241–250|access-date=2012-10-25|archive-date=2012-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114191419/http://cat.inist.fr/?aModele=afficheN&cpsidt=18172400|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>而無性戀者們可能會將無性戀定義為"指缺乏或少有性慾、性吸引、性行為，僅僅享受[[浪漫|浪漫]]的戀愛關係"。<span data-segmentid="28" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Prause2" /><ref name="Fischer">{{Cite book|last=Nancy L. Fischer|last2=Steven Seidman|title=Introducing the New Sexuality Studies|isbn=978-1317449188|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2016|page=183|accessdate=2017-01-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SEmTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA183|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726102104/https://books.google.com/books?id=SEmTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA183|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>但無性戀者們也可能會因自身的認同而有著與彼此不同的定義。<span data-segmentid="29" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Fischer" /></span>

<span data-segmentid="30" class="cx-segment">The Asexual Visibility and Education Network（AVEN）將無性戀定義為"指一個人不感受到性吸引力"，並發表了 "又一個截然不同的性少數民族誕生了，他們在發現和探索自己的性取向時短暫的稱呼自己為無性戀" 以及 "並沒有一個像石蕊試紙一樣的東西能夠直接確定一個人是否為無性戀。無性戀就像其他的性向認同一樣 — 它的核心概念只是一個人們用來尋找自我的詞。如果有人覺得無性戀這個詞很適合用來表達他們自己，我們十分鼓勵他們去使用這個詞彙。<span data-segmentid="32" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Overview2">{{cite web|title=Overview|url=http://www.asexuality.org/home/?q=overview.html|accessdate=2016-01-06|year=2008|publisher=The Asexual Visibility and Education Network|archive-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119005301/http://www.asexuality.org/home/?q=overview.html|dead-url=no}}</ref></span></span>

<span data-segmentid="33" class="cx-segment">雖然無性戀者一般不感受到性吸引，只想投入純粹的浪漫關係，<ref name="Sex and society3">{{Cite book|editor-last=Marshall Cavendish|title=Asexuality|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|accessdate=2013-07-27|volume=2|year=2010|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7906-2|pages=82–83|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016040824/https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Richards and Barker">{{Cite book|last=Christina Richards|last2=Meg Barker|title=Sexuality and Gender for Mental Health Professionals: A Practical Guide|isbn=978-1-4462-9313-3|publisher=[[Sage_Publications|SAGE]]|year=2013|pages=124–127|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uSiXAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT124|archive-date=2014-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728200354/http://books.google.com/books?id=uSiXAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT124|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>但還是有一些無性戀提出他們會感受到性吸引，只是對於性行為不感興趣，另外也有些無性戀者喜歡一些親密而非性的肢體動作，如：擁抱、接吻、牽手。<span data-segmentid="35" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Halter2">{{Cite book|last=Margaret Jordan Halter|last2=Elizabeth M. Varcarolis|title=Varcarolis' Foundations of Psychiatric Mental Health Nursing|isbn=978-1-4557-5358-1|publisher=[[Elsevier_Health_Sciences|Elsevier Health Sciences]]|year=2013|page=382|accessdate=2014-05-07|url=https://books.google.com/?id=mZ15AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA382#v=onepage|archive-date=2020-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414120344/https://books.google.com/books?id=mZ15AAAAQBAJ&pg=PA382&hl=en#v=onepage|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Prause3">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: Classification and Characterization|url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|last=Prause|first=Nicole|last2=Cynthia A. Graham|date=August 2004|journal=[[Archives_of_Sexual_Behavior|Archives of Sexual Behavior]]|accessdate=2007-08-31|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10508-006-9142-3|volume=36|pages=341–356|pmid=17345167|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927014407/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|archivedate=2007-09-27|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref name="Cerankowski and Milks2">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>一些無性戀可能會因好奇心而參與性活動，<span data-segmentid="36" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Prause3" /></span>也有些會藉由[[自慰|自慰]]來發洩性慾，而其他的無性戀則不認為有必要這麼做。<span data-segmentid="37" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Cerankowski and Milks3">{{cite book|author=Karli June Cerankowski|author2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="New Scientist3">{{cite web|title=Feature: Glad to be asexual|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn6533|accessdate=2007-11-11|author=Westphal, Sylvia Pagan|work=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219003148/http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn6533|archivedate=2007-12-19|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="Bridgeman3">{{cite news|first=Shelley|last=Bridgeman|title=No sex please, we're asexual|date=2007-08-05|work=[[The_New_Zealand_Herald|The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=2011-09-16|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=10455823&pnum=0|archive-date=2018-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181103013612/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=10455823&pnum=0|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>

<span data-segmentid="39" class="cx-segment">關於無性戀的性活動特別的是，對於[[自慰|自慰]]的需求或慾望普遍被無性戀們稱為[[性衝動|性衝動]]，他們不認為自慰是因為感受到了性吸引，或是因為一個人是有性戀；會進行自慰的無性戀通常認為它是一個自然現象，並不是自己可能是有性戀的象徵，並且可能不覺得自慰是愉快的。<ref name="Prause4">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: Classification and Characterization|url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|last=Prause|first=Nicole|last2=Cynthia A. Graham|date=August 2004|journal=[[Archives_of_Sexual_Behavior|Archives of Sexual Behavior]]|accessdate=2007-08-31|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10508-006-9142-3|volume=36|pages=341–356|pmid=17345167|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927014407/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|archivedate=2007-09-27|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Sexual fantasy and masturbation among asexual individuals|last=Yule|first=Morag A.|last2=Brotto|first2=Lori A.|journal=The Canadian Journal of Human Sexuality|issue=2|doi=10.3138/cjhs.2409|year=2014|volume=23|pages=89–95|last3=Gorzalka|first3=Boris B.}}</ref></span><span data-segmentid="41" class="cx-segment">而一些無性戀則可能有[[勃起功能障礙|勃起功能障礙]]，參與性活動對它們來說是不可能的。<ref name="More to life">{{Cite journal|title=There's More to Life Than Just Sex? Difference and Commonality Within the Asexual Community|last=Carrigan|first=Mark|date=August 2011|journal=Sexualities|issue=4|doi=10.1177/1363460711406462|volume=14|pages=462–478}}</ref>無性戀各自對性行為的想法都不同；有些人可能會和伴侶發生性行為，但他們對於性行為很冷漠；有些則是強烈反對發生性行為，但是無性戀通常並不會因為別人有性行為而討厭他們。</span><span data-segmentid="42" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Prause4" /><ref name="Cerankowski and Milks4">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Bridgeman">{{Cite news|first=Shelley|author=Bridgeman|title=No sex please, we're asexual|date=2007-08-05|work=[[The_New_Zealand_Herald|The New Zealand Herald]]|accessdate=2011-09-16|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=10455823&pnum=0|archive-date=2018-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181103013612/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/lifestyle/news/article.cfm?c_id=6&objectid=10455823&pnum=0|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>

<span data-segmentid="43" class="cx-segment">無性戀們有著一些自己的性向標籤，這些標籤同時表明了他們的性別認同以及浪漫傾向。</span><span data-segmentid="44" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Padraig">{{Cite journal|title=Freedom, Invisibility, and Community: A Qualitative Study of Self-Identification with Asexuality|last=MacNeela|first=Pádraig|last2=Murphy|first2=Aisling|date=2014-12-30|journal=Archives of Sexual Behavior|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10508-014-0458-0|volume=44|pages=799–812|language=en|issn=0004-0002|pmid=25548065}}</ref></span> 他們有可能使用一些已經存在的有性戀的性取向標籤來表明身分<span data-segmentid="46" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Overview">{{Cite web|title=Overview|url=http://www.asexuality.org/home/?q=overview.html|accessdate=2016-01-06|year=2008|publisher=The Asexual Visibility and Education Network|archive-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119005301/http://www.asexuality.org/home/?q=overview.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Richards and Barker2">{{Cite book|last=Christina Richards|last2=Meg Barker|title=Sexuality and Gender for Mental Health Professionals: A Practical Guide|isbn=978-1-4462-9313-3|publisher=[[Sage_Publications|SAGE]]|year=2013|pages=124–127|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uSiXAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT124|archive-date=2014-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728200354/http://books.google.com/books?id=uSiXAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT124|dead-url=no}}</ref></span>，或者使用他們自己的術語。無性戀的術語中，[[性取向|性取向]]（sexual）被替換成了[[浪漫傾向|浪漫傾向]]（romantic）<span data-segmentid="46" class="cx-segment"><ref name="Cerankowski and Milks5">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Richards and Barker2" /></span>，如：

* 無浪漫傾向（aromantic）：不感受到浪漫吸引力
* 雙性浪漫傾向（biromantic）：類似於雙性戀
* 異性浪漫傾向（heteroromantic）：類似於異性戀
* 同性浪漫傾向（homoromantic）：類似於同性戀
* 泛性浪漫傾向（panromantic）：類似於泛性戀

有些人可能會認同自己是[[灰色性向|灰色性向]]，灰色性向可以包涵灰色浪漫傾向、半浪漫傾向、半性向（demisexual、semisexual）等，他們認為自己介於無浪漫傾向及浪漫傾向之間，或是介於無性戀及有性戀之間。demisexual可能會在與人建立了很深的情感聯繫後而感受到[[性吸引|性吸引]]或[[性慾|性慾]]<ref name="Cerankowski and Milks6">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Adler|first=Melissa|title=Serving LGBTIQ Library and Archives Users|year=2010|editor-first=Ellen|editor-last=Greenblatt|publisher=[[McFarland_&_Company|McFarland & Company]]|location=[[North_Carolina|North Carolina]]|isbn=978-0-7864-4894-4}}</ref>，而semisexual則是指一個人只感受到[[性衝動|性衝動]]，對別人卻無法感受到[[性吸引|性吸引]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=I need help figuring out a definition for semisexuality|url=http://demigrace.forumotion.com/t108-i-need-help-figuring-out-a-definition-for-semisexuality|accessdate=2019-07-08|work=demigrace.forumotion.com|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128115516/https://demigrace.forumotion.com/t108-i-need-help-figuring-out-a-definition-for-semisexuality|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Urban Dictionary: semisexual|url=https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=semisexual|accessdate=2019-07-08|work=Urban Dictionary|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421045209/https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=semisexual|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Demisexual/Semisexual?|url=https://www.asexuality.org/en/topic/78254-demisexualsemisexual/|accessdate=2019-07-08|work=Asexual Visibility and Education Network|language=en-US|archive-date=2019-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708221726/https://www.asexuality.org/en/topic/78254-demisexualsemisexual/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在無性戀社群中還存在一些無性戀者自行發明的術語，如friend-focused，代表超越友情的非浪漫關係。另一些術語像是squashes和zucchinis（[[西葫蘆|西葫蘆]]），分別代表非浪漫的戀愛以及[[酷兒柏拉圖式關係|酷兒柏拉圖式關係]]。還有non-asexual及allosexual等詞彙借代有性戀的人。<ref name="ReferenceA">{{Cite journal|title=Making Sense in and of the Asexual Community: Navigating Relationships and Identities in a Context of Resistance|url=|last=Chasin|first=CJ DeLuzio|journal=Journal of Community & Applied Social Psychology|issue=2|doi=10.1002/casp.2203|year=2015|volume=25|pages=167–180|issn=1099-1298}}</ref>有些無性戀用撲克牌的王牌（ace）來表明他們的浪漫傾向，像是用黑桃A來表示自己是無浪漫傾向者，用紅心A表示自己有浪漫傾向。<ref name="AceSuits">{{Cite book|last=Julie Sondra Decker|title=The Invisible Orientation: An Introduction to Asexuality|date=2015|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=9781510700642|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vTSCDwAAQBAJ&dq=ace+of+hearts+asexual&q=ace+of+hearts#v=snippet&q=ace%20of%20hearts&f=false|accessdate=2019-04-20|archive-date=2020-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803043357/https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vTSCDwAAQBAJ&dq=ace+of+hearts+asexual&q=ace+of+hearts#v=snippet&q=ace%20of%20hearts&f=false|dead-url=no}}{{Page needed}}</ref>

== 研究 ==
