=== 流行度 ===
無性戀不是一個新的傾向，只是"無性戀"這個詞相對較新穎而已。<ref name="Sesmith">{{Cite news|first=S. E.|author=Smith|title=Asexuality always existed, you just didn't notice it|publisher=''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''|date=2012-08-21|accessdate=2013-03-11|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2012/aug/21/asexuality-always-existed-asexual|work=The Guardian|archive-date=2015-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150408115642/http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2012/aug/21/asexuality-always-existed-asexual|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[英國衛報|英國衛報]]的S·E·史密斯說無性戀的人數不見得有增加，可能只是無性戀的能見度增加了。<ref name="Sesmith" /> [[阿爾弗雷德·金賽|阿爾弗雷德·金賽]]的[[金賽量表|金賽量表]]將人依據對異性及同性的性反應分為0到6級，並加入了一個「X」等級來表示「沒有社會性的聯繫或反應的人」，<ref name="Kinsey-male">{{Cite book|first=Alfred C.|last=Kinsey|year=1948|title=Sexual Behavior in the Human Male|url=https://archive.org/details/sexualbehaviorin0000unse|publisher=W.B. Saunders|isbn=978-0-253-33412-1}}</ref><ref name="Kinsey-female">{{Cite book|first=Alfred C.|last=Kinsey|year=1953|title=Sexual Behavior in the Human Female|url=https://archive.org/details/sexualbehaviorin00inst|publisher=W.B. Saunders|isbn=978-0-253-33411-4}}</ref> 而在現代，這被歸類為了無性戀。<ref name="Stange">{{Cite book|last=Mary Zeiss Stange|last2=Carol K. Oyster|last3=Jane E. Sloan|title=Encyclopedia of Women in Today's World|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bOkPjFQoBj8C&pg=PA158|accessdate=2013-07-27|date=2011-02-23|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=978-1-4129-7685-5|page=158|archive-date=2020-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914220425/https://books.google.com/books?id=bOkPjFQoBj8C&pg=PA158|dead-url=no}}</ref>學者Justin J. Lehmiller 指出：「金賽量表的X分類強調了缺少性行為，而現代定義則是強調無性戀是缺少性吸引。因此，金賽量表對於無性戀來說可能不準確。」<ref name="Lehmiller">{{Cite book|last=Justin J. Lehmiller|title=The Psychology of Human Sexuality|publisher=[[John_Wiley_&_Sons|John Wiley & Sons]]|isbn=978-1119164708|page=250|date=2017|accessdate=2017-11-29|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ytk5DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT250|archive-date=2021-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320135007/https://books.google.com/books?id=ytk5DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT250|dead-url=no}}</ref>金賽將1.5%的成年男性歸類在了X，<ref name="Kinsey-male" /><ref name="Kinsey-female" /> 在[[金賽報告|金賽報告]]的第二本書"女性性行為"中，他細分了各種人被歸類在X的比例：未婚女性 = 14-19%，已婚女性 = 1-3%，曾經有過婚姻的女性 = 5-8%，未婚男性 = 5-8%，已婚男性 = 0%，曾經有過婚姻的男性 = 1-2%<ref name="Kinsey-female" />

在1994年，關於無性戀的人數有了更進一步的數據，一個[[英國|英國]]的研究團隊因為[[愛滋病|愛滋病]]的流行而對18,876名英國受訪者做了全面的問卷調查。問卷中包含了一道關於性吸引的題目，結果1.05%的受訪者回答了「從未感受過性吸引。」<ref>Wellings, K. (1994). ''Sexual Behaviour in Britain: The National Survey of Sexual Attitudes and Lifestyles.'' [[Penguin_Books|Penguin Books]].</ref>之後，加拿大的性研究者{{le|安東尼·博加特|Anthony Bogaert}}從2004年開始進行了對於這個現象的一系列研究，安東尼·博格特的研究指出了1%的英國人不感受到性吸引，但他相信不只有1%的人是無性戀，他注意到了30%原本要加入調查的人選擇了退出，而其中許多是對於性行為較不感興趣的人，因為無性戀在參與者中比較容易被忽視。同一個研究中的同性戀和雙性戀人數也只有約1.1%，比其他研究指出的比例少了很多。<ref name="Bogaert20042">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: prevalence and associated factors in a national probability sample|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-sex-research_2004-08_41_3/page/279|last=Bogaert|first=Anthony F.|journal=[[Journal_of_Sex_Research|Journal of Sex Research]]|issue=3|doi=10.1080/00224490409552235|year=2004|volume=41|pages=279–87|pmid=15497056}}</ref><ref name="Bogaert20062">{{Cite journal|title=Toward a conceptual understanding of asexuality|url=http://cat.inist.fr/?aModele=afficheN&cpsidt=18172400|last=Bogaert|first=Anthony F.|journal=[[Review_of_General_Psychology|Review of General Psychology]]|issue=3|doi=10.1037/1089-2680.10.3.241|year=2006|volume=10|pages=241–250|access-date=2012-10-25|archive-date=2012-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114191419/http://cat.inist.fr/?aModele=afficheN&cpsidt=18172400|dead-url=no}}</ref>

對比安東尼·博格特的數據，一個2013年發表的研究指出，根據於2000-2001年進行的《英國全國性態度和生活形態調查》（The National Survey of Sexual Attitudes and Lifestyles）的數據，在16-44歲的英國人間無性戀的流行度只有0.4%。<ref name="Fischer2">{{Cite book|last=Nancy L. Fischer|last2=Steven Seidman|title=Introducing the New Sexuality Studies|isbn=978-1317449188|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2016|page=183|accessdate=2017-01-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SEmTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA183|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726102104/https://books.google.com/books?id=SEmTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA183|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Who reports absence of sexual attraction in Britain? Evidence from national probability surveys|url=http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/1301794/|last=Aicken|first=Catherine R. H.|last2=Mercer|first2=Catherine H.|date=2013-05-01|journal=Psychology & Sexuality|issue=2|doi=10.1080/19419899.2013.774161|volume=4|pages=121–135|issn=1941-9899|last3=Cassell|first3=Jackie A.|access-date=2019-07-12|archive-date=2019-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923043744/http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/1301794/|dead-url=no}}</ref>這個數字和10年前的首次《英國全國性態度和生活形態調查》在同年齡層中的數據0.9%相差不少。<ref name=":02">{{Cite journal|title=Who reports absence of sexual attraction in Britain? Evidence from national probability surveys|url=http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/1301794/|last=Aicken|first=Catherine R. H.|last2=Mercer|first2=Catherine H.|date=2013-05-01|journal=Psychology & Sexuality|issue=2|doi=10.1080/19419899.2013.774161|volume=4|pages=121–135|issn=1941-9899|last3=Cassell|first3=Jackie A.|access-date=2019-07-12|archive-date=2019-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923043744/http://discovery.ucl.ac.uk/1301794/|dead-url=no}}</ref>安東尼·博格特在2015年時也發現了兩次調查間之間數據的減少。<ref name="bogaert2015">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: What It Is and Why It Matters|last=Bogaert|first=A. F.|journal=Journal of Sex Research|issue=4|doi=10.1080/00224499.2015.1015713|year=2015|volume=52|pages=362–379|pmid=25897566}}</ref>此外艾肯、默瑟、卡塞爾發現了不同種族的受訪者之中存在不感受到性吸引的人的比例差異的證據；不論男女，來自[[印度|印度]]和[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]的人較有可能不感受到性吸引力。<ref name=":0" />

[[YouGov|YouGov]]在2015年進行的一項調查中，1,632名英國成年人被要求根據金賽量表將自己分至其中一類，1%的參與者選擇了"無性向"。共佔0%的男性，2%的女性。<ref>{{Cite web|title=1 in 2 young people say they are not 100% heterosexual|url=https://yougov.co.uk/topics/lifestyle/articles-reports/2015/08/16/half-young-not-heterosexual|accessdate=2018-12-31|date=2015-08-16|format=PDF|archive-date=2021-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210409173050/https://yougov.co.uk/topics/lifestyle/articles-reports/2015/08/16/half-young-not-heterosexual|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 性取向及心理健康 ===
學者之間對於無性戀是否算是一種性取向有著很大的爭議。<ref name="Sexual orientation2">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality gets more attention, but is it a sexual orientation?|url=http://www.apositive.org/wordpress_backup/?page_id=222|last=Melby|first=Todd|date=November 2005|journal=Contemporary Sexuality|accessdate=2016-02-06|issue=11|volume=39|pages=1, 4–5|issn=1094-5725|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106135903/http://www.apositive.org/wordpress_backup/?page_id=222|archivedate=2015-11-06|postscript=  [http://journalseek.net/cgi-bin/journalseek/journalsearch.cgi?field=title&query=1094-5725 The journal currently does not have a website]}}</ref><ref name="Sex and society4">{{Cite book|editor-last=Marshall Cavendish|title=Asexuality|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|accessdate=2013-07-27|volume=2|year=2010|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7906-2|pages=82–83|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016040824/https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|dead-url=no}}</ref>無性戀被一些學者與[[性欲機能減退障礙|性欲機能減退障礙]]（HSDD）比較並畫上了等號，因為兩者都是缺少感受性吸引的能力，HSDD被用來[[醫療化|醫療化]]了無性戀，但是無性戀通常不被認為是一種疾病或是[[性功能障礙|性功能障礙]]（像是[[性高潮障礙|性高潮障礙]]、[[性感缺乏|性感缺乏]]等），因為一個無性戀者不一定有醫學上的障礙或是社交障礙。<ref name="DePaulo2">{{Cite magazine}}</ref><ref name="Richards and Barker3">{{Cite book|last=Christina Richards|last2=Meg Barker|title=Sexuality and Gender for Mental Health Professionals: A Practical Guide|isbn=978-1-4462-9313-3|publisher=[[Sage_Publications|SAGE]]|year=2013|pages=124–127|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uSiXAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT124|archive-date=2014-07-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728200354/http://books.google.com/books?id=uSiXAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT124|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Reconsidering Asexuality">{{Cite journal|title=Reconsidering Asexuality and Its Radical Potential|url=http://cj.chasin.ca/Chasin_Reconsidering.Asexuality_FS.Vol39.2_2013.pdf|last=Chasin|first=CJ DeLuzio|date=2013|journal=Feminist Studies|accessdate=2014-04-29|issue=2|volume=39|page=405|archive-date=2014-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303164252/http://cj.chasin.ca/Chasin_Reconsidering.Asexuality_FS.Vol39.2_2013.pdf|dead-url=yes}}</ref>不同於HSDD，無性戀一般不會因為性方面的事情感到「顯著的痛苦」、感到具有社交困難，或是缺少性刺激；無性戀被認為是持久的無法感受到性吸引。<ref name="Bogaert20063">{{Cite journal|title=Toward a conceptual understanding of asexuality|url=http://cat.inist.fr/?aModele=afficheN&cpsidt=18172400|last=Bogaert|first=Anthony F.|journal=[[Review_of_General_Psychology|Review of General Psychology]]|issue=3|doi=10.1037/1089-2680.10.3.241|year=2006|volume=10|pages=241–250|access-date=2012-10-25|archive-date=2012-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120114191419/http://cat.inist.fr/?aModele=afficheN&cpsidt=18172400|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Richards and Barker3" />一個研究發現和HSDD比較起來，無性戀者較沒有性欲、性經驗、對於性的負面情緒以及憂鬱症狀。<ref name="brotto2015">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: An Extreme Variant of Sexual Desire Disorder?|last=Brotto, L. A.|last2=Yule, M. A.|journal=The Journal of Sexual Medicine|issue=3|doi=10.1111/jsm.12806|year=2015|volume=12|pages=646–660|pmid=25545124|last3=Gorzalka, B..B.}}</ref> 研究人員說，無性戀中並沒有包含異常比例的[[述情障礙|述情障礙]]、[[憂鬱症|憂鬱症]]或是[[人格障礙|人格障礙]]族群。<ref name="Richards and Barker3" />並且有些人就算自己無性的狀態被以上述症狀作為解釋，仍然堅持著自己的無性戀身分。<ref name="Cerankowski and Milks 2">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|page=246|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XbgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT246|archive-date=2015-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150912115307/https://books.google.com/books?id=XbgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT246|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 性 ===
有些無性戀可能會藉由自慰來發洩性欲，或藉由性行為來取悅伴侶（見上文）。<ref name="Prause5">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: Classification and Characterization|url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|last=Prause|first=Nicole|last2=Cynthia A. Graham|date=August 2004|journal=[[Archives_of_Sexual_Behavior|Archives of Sexual Behavior]]|accessdate=2007-08-31|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10508-006-9142-3|volume=36|pages=341–356|pmid=17345167|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927014407/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|archivedate=2007-09-27|deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref name="Cerankowski and Milks7">{{Cite book|last=Karli June Cerankowski|last2=Megan Milks|title=Asexualities: Feminist and Queer Perspectives|isbn=978-1-134-69253-8|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2014|pages=89–93|accessdate=2014-07-03|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|archive-date=2014-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140716130847/http://books.google.com/books?id=zLgTAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA89|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="New Scientist">{{Cite web|title=Feature: Glad to be asexual|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn6533|accessdate=2007-11-11|author=Westphal, Sylvia Pagan|work=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071219003148/http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn6533|archivedate=2007-12-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>Fischer等人報告了：「研究無性戀者生理的學者們指出，無性戀者是會有性[[喚醒|喚醒]]的，但是可能並不會有[[主觀體驗|主觀體驗]]。也就是說，就算身體發生了性喚醒，在心理及情感層面可能還是不會受到喚醒。」<ref name="Fischer3">{{Cite book|last=Nancy L. Fischer|last2=Steven Seidman|title=Introducing the New Sexuality Studies|isbn=978-1317449188|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|year=2016|page=183|accessdate=2017-01-04|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SEmTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA183|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726102104/https://books.google.com/books?id=SEmTDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA183|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2007年的一個由[[金賽性、性別與生殖研究中心|金賽研究所]]贊助的小測試中，發現了無性戀者「對於和伴侶發生性行為有著較少的慾望並且較少受到性喚醒，但是對於自慰的慾望和抑制能力與有性戀者相差不大」。<ref name="Prause6">{{Cite journal|title=Asexuality: Classification and Characterization|url=http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|last=Prause|first=Nicole|last2=Cynthia A. Graham|date=August 2004|journal=[[Archives_of_Sexual_Behavior|Archives of Sexual Behavior]]|accessdate=2007-08-31|issue=3|doi=10.1007/s10508-006-9142-3|volume=36|pages=341–356|pmid=17345167|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927014407/http://www.kinseyinstitute.org/publications/PDF/PrauseGrahamPDF.pdf|archivedate=2007-09-27|deadurl=yes}}</ref>
