=== 主流文化 ===
目前還很少關於無性戀社群歷史的研究。<ref name="Anthology">{{Cite book|last=Carrigan|first=Mark|last2=Gupta|first2=Kristina|last3=Morrison|first3=Todd G.|year=2015|title=Asexuality and Sexual Normativity: An Anthology|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=sEGDCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT77|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-415-73132-4|access-date=2019-07-12|archive-date=2020-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530074809/https://books.google.es/books?id=sEGDCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT77|dead-url=no}}</ref>在1990年代時，就已經有一些關於缺少性欲的人的私人網站，<ref name="Sigusch">[[世集团董事会主席沃尔克马Sigusch|Volkmar Sigusch]]. "Sexualitäten: Eine kritische Theorie in 99 Fragmenten". 2013. {{Interlanguage link multi|Campus Verlag|de|Campus Verlag}}.</ref>但是學者們說由自稱無性戀的人組成的社群僅能追溯到21世紀初，因為當時的[[虛擬社群|虛擬社群]]變得更受歡迎。<ref name="Oleksy">{{Cite book|last=Elżbieta H. Oleksy|last2=Aleksandra M. Różalska|last3=Marek M. Wojtaszek|title=The Personal of the Political: Transgenerational Dialogues in Contemporary European Feminisms|isbn=978-1443884457|publisher=[[Cambridge_Scholars_Publishing|Cambridge Scholars Publishing]]|year=2015|page=13|accessdate=2017-10-05|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KZ7WCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA13|quote=The emergence of asexual community at the cusp of the twenty-first century came as a surprise for social scientists. Asexuals, people who experience no sexual attraction, have started to build an online community and form a cohesive sexual identity inspired by the emancipation of other LGBTQ movements. [...] The socio-cultural circumstances conducive to the constitution of asexual identity at the dawn of the twenty-first century.|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726102012/https://books.google.com/books?id=KZ7WCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Goldberg">{{Cite book|last=Abbie E. Goldberg|title=The SAGE Encyclopedia of LGBTQ Studies|isbn=978-1483371290|publisher=[[SAGE_Publications|SAGE Publications]]|year=2016|page=92|accessdate=2017-10-05|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=736zDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA92|quote=[...] The sociological literature has stressed the novelty of asexuality as a distinctive form of social identification that emerged in the early 21st century.|archive-date=2020-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200726100530/https://books.google.com/books?id=736zDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA92|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[Volkmar_Sigusch|Volkmar Sigusch]]說當時有一些像是「Leather Spinsters」的無性戀團體，還有Geraldin van Vilsteren在[[荷蘭|荷蘭]]建立的「Nonlibidoism Society」（無性欲者社區），在[[Yahoo|Yahoo! Groups]]上也有一個叫做「Haven for the Human Amoeba」的無性戀社群。<ref name="Sigusch" />The '''Asexual Visibility and Education Network'''（AVEN）則是由[[美國|美國]]的無性戀的[[行動主義|行動主義]]者[[大衛·傑|大衛·傑]]在2001年創立的一個針對無性戀議題的組織。<ref name="Sex and society5">{{Cite book|editor-last=Marshall Cavendish|title=Asexuality|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|accessdate=2013-07-27|volume=2|year=2010|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-7906-2|pages=82–83|archive-date=2015-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151016040824/https://books.google.com/books?id=aVDZchwkIMEC&pg=PA82|dead-url=no}}</ref>它的目標是「建立大眾對無性戀的接受、討論無性戀問題以及促進無性戀社會的成長」。<ref name="Sex and society5" /><ref name="Swash2">{{Cite news|first=Rosie|author=Swash|title=Among the asexuals|publisher=''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''|date=2012-02-25|accessdate=2013-02-02|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2012/feb/26/among-the-asexuals|work=The Guardian|archive-date=2021-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211010222/http://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2012/feb/26/among-the-asexuals|dead-url=no}}</ref>





